h a combined installed capacity of  megawatts in france its customers include silicone chemical aluminum and steel manufacturers auto companies and their suppliers ductile iron foundries manufacturers of photovoltaic solar cells and computer chips and concrete producers the company was formerly known as velonewco limited ferroglobe plc was incorporated in  and is headquartered in london the united kingdom ferroglobe plc is a subsidiary of grupo villar mir sa the following firms have also recently changed their position in gsm as of quarter end sprott inc had sold  shares trimming its holdings by  the value of the total investment in ferroglobe plc – ordinary share decreased from  to  a change of  quarter over quarter as of the end of the quarter bank of montreal can had disposed of a total of  shares trimming its position  the value in dollars went from  to  decreasing  since the last quarter morgan stanley expanded its investment by buying  shares an increase of  as of  morgan stanley now controls  shares worth  the total value of its holdings increased  as of the end of the quarter tower research capital llc trc had acquired a total of  shares growing its stake by  the value of the investment in ferroglobe plc – ordinary share went from  to  a change of  quarter to quarter on september  the company was changed to a “buy” by baird up from the previous “” rating on august   the stock rating was rated “neutral” according to a b riley report which was a cut from the previous “buy” rating on june   the stock rating was set at “buy” in a report from jefferies a boost from the previous “hold” rating on march  jp morgan made no change to the stock rating of “overweight” and lowered the price target to  from  december  investment analysts at b riley  co maintained a stock rating of “buy” but moved down the price target from  to  november  investment analysts at b riley made no change to the company rating of “buy” but lowered the price target to  from  in the latest earnin